definitions.definition: Ellipsis of genitive case ( “ a grammatical case used to express a relationship of origin or possession ” ) .
A word inflected in the genitive case, and which thus indicates origin or possession.

main_definition: ( countable , uncountable ) Ellipsis of genitive case ( “ a grammatical case used to express a relationship of origin or possession ” ) .
